questions.title:
Consider the following class representing a player in a video game with a name, number of lives, and points. You want to add a method to transfer a given amount of points from one player to another. You can assume this amount is always valid.
class Player:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name
        self.points = 1000
        self.lives = 3

options:
def transfer(self, player, points):
    self.points = points
    player.points = points

def transfer(self, player, points):
    self.points -= points
    player.points += points

questions.title:
You are given a class representing a recipe, which stores its ingredients in a dictionary mapping ingredient names to quantities. You want to add a method that increases the quantity of an ingredient if it already exists, or creates it if it does not.
class Recipe:
    def __init__(self, name, ingredients):
        # ingredients is a dict like {"flour": 200, "eggs": 3}
        self.name = name
        self.ingredients = ingredients

options:
def add_ingredient(self, name, amount):
    if name in amount:
        amount[name] += self.ingredients

def add_ingredient(self, name, amount):
    if name in self.ingredients:
        self.ingredients[name] += amount
    else:
        self.ingredients[name] = amount

